## üêö Linux Shell Commands

| Command        | Description                                                                 |
|----------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `pwd`          | Print the current working directory (shows where you are).                   |
| `cd`           | Change directory.                                                            |
| `ls`           | List files and directories.                                                  |
| `rm`           | Remove files (use `rm -r` for directories). ‚ö†Ô∏è Be careful!                   |
| `cp`           | Copy files or directories.                                                   |
| `mv`           | Move or rename files/directories.                                            |
| `mkdir`        | Create a new directory.                                                      |
| `{num1..num2}` | Brace expansion ‚Äî creates a range of numbers (e.g., `mkdir folder{1..5}`).   |
| `*.txt`        | Wildcard ‚Äî matches all `.txt` files in a directory.                          |


## ‚úçÔ∏è Vim Basics

| Command       | Description                                                                 |
|----------------|------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| `yy`          | Yank (copy) a line.                                                          |
| `p`           | Paste after the cursor.                                                      |
| `gg`          | Go to the top of the file.                                                   |
| `G`           | Go to the bottom of the file.                                                |
| `dd`          | Delete (cut) a line.                                                         |
| `numberyy`    | Copy that many lines (e.g., `3yy` copies 3 lines).                           |
| `numberdd`    | Delete that many lines (e.g., `5dd` deletes 5 lines).                        |
| `/text`       | Search for the word ‚Äútext‚Äù in the file.                                      |
| `n` / `N`     | Jump to the next / previous search match.                                    |
